# Per-run JSON reports written by `npm run eval`. Build artifacts keyed by
# run_id; grow unboundedly and are not meant to be committed by default.
# The CI workflow uploads them as artifacts on failure (see
# .github/workflows/agentforge-eval.yml) — that is the canonical archive
# surface for CI runs.
reports/

# Exception: a small set of *canonical evidence* reports are committed by
# force (`git add -f reports/<file>`) at submission-style milestones so
# graders have a fixed, version-controlled snapshot to inspect. Today the
# canonical evidence is the W2 judge-populated 88-case run. The `eval_status`
# HTTP endpoint sorts reports by the run-id timestamp embedded in the
# filename, so adding a newer committed report (with a later timestamp
# prefix) is enough to update what the live endpoint serves.
